attributes.background:
It is proposed that an annual review be undertaken by an all-ranks veteran committee to establish an enhanced benefits package that ex-Service personnel would be entitled to upon entering civilian life.

While a non-exclusive list, these benefits could include the introduction of priority treatment in medical and public services waiting lists;
military wings added to major regional hospitals with appropriately trained medical staff;
improved social services and mental health support;
a marketing campaign to promote the high calibre of former service personnel to employers;
a golden hello incentive for businesses employing veterans;
a positive discrimination policy in favour of employing veterans by the public sector;
a preferential tax support package;
restructuring of the military pension regulations;
a UK Veterans ID card; and allowing access to veterans to military sports and recreational facilities.

This action would serve to introduce an element of parity between UK ex-service personnel and veterans in comparative nations, and would be appropriate recognition by the Government of the service given by veterans of the UK Armed Forces.
